[
  "Ernest Garcia III is the CEO and cofounder of Carvana, an ecommerce platform for buying and selling used cars. \r\n",
  "Garcia started Carvana in 2012 as a subsidiary of DriveTime, a traditional used car business that operates 138 dealerships in 26 states.\r\n",
  "Garcia started Carvana as a way to sell used cars directly instead of relying on middlemen; the company also offers financing services.",
  "The younger Garcia struck out on his own in 2017, spinning Carvana out of Drivetime in an IPO that raised $225 million.\r\n",
  "His father, Ernest Garcia II, owns and runs DriveTime, and helped fund the initial development of Carvana; he remains its largest shareholder. "
]